{
  "texts": [
    "It focuses on sentences containing textually ambiguous words (in terms of gender) in the English source and provides the possible translation alternatives (in terms of binary gender) 24 on the Italian target side.",
    "Two example of tagged sentences from the gENder-IT corpus are provided below for illustration.",
    "The first one, Example 1, only contains <F> tags since the gender of 'ambiguous' words such as 'I' can be determined based on sentence context.",
    "Example 2, is one where within the sentence context, no assumption can or should be made with respect to the gender of the referent.",
    "To indicate that not all ambiguous words have the same referent, numbers are appended (e.g."
  ]
